whereas.text:
Whereas hailed for her talents as a performing artist at an early age, Maya Angelou toured Europe
			 with a production of the Gershwin opera Porgy and Bess in 1955 and
			 released her first album in 1957;

Whereas in 1969, Maya Angelou wrote the autobiography I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings, which
			 catapulted her to international acclaim for its vivid and honest depiction
			 of the experience of black women in the Jim Crow era;

Whereas Maya Angelou has published more than 30 best-selling titles, including her collection of
			 poems, Just Give Me a Cool Drink of Water ‘fore I Diiie, which earned
			 her a Pulitzer Prize nomination;

Whereas Maya Angelou was honored with the Presidential Medal of Freedom in 2011, the Lincoln Medal
			 in 2008, and the National Medal of Arts in 2000 for her exceptional
			 contributions to American culture as an author and poet;
